title: Short Story Collection Vol. 053
creator: Various
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox Short Story Collection Vol. 053, read by LibriVox volunteers. A collection of 20 short works of fiction in the public domain read by a group of LibriVox members, including short stories by Melville, Blackwood, Hawthorne, Dostoyevsky, Wilde and Thomas Hood. This collection comprises: 01 - The Piazza by Herman Melville (1819-1891) 02 - The Lightning-Rod Man by Herman Melville (1819-1891) 03 - The Bell-Tower by Herman Melville (1819-1891) 04 - Titbottom's Spectacles by George William Curtis (1824-1892) 05 - On the Gulls’ Road by Willa Cather (1873-1947) 06 - The Olive by Algernon Blackwood (1869-1951) 07 - The Haunted Mind by Nathaniel Hawthorne (1804-1864) 08 - Romance in Encyclopaedialand by Robert C Benchley (1889-1943) 09 - The Trousseau by Anton Chekhov (1860-1904) 10 - The Star-Child by Oscar Wilde (1854-1900) 11 - The Squire by Elsie Singmaster (1878–1958) 12 - The Peasant Marey by Fyodor Dostoyevsky (1821-1881) 13 - Autumn Holiday by Sarah Orne Jewett (1849-1909) 14 - Rappacinni's Daughter by Nathaniel Hawthorne (1804-1864) 15 - The Golden Cup And The Dish Of Silver by Thomas Hood (1799–1845) 16 - The Widow of Galicia by Thomas Hood (1799–1845) 17 - A Wireless Message by Ambrose Bierce (1842-1913?) 18 - The Hydrophobic Skunk by Irvin S. Cobb (1876-1944) 19 - The Ole Virginia by Stewart Edward White (1873-1946) 20 - The Million Dollar Freight Train by Frank Spearman (1859-1937) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
